snippet: The delay raised questions about whether Syria can meet an extended deadline of April 27 to export its chemical weapons arsenal for destruction.
abstract: Syria has delivered a consignment of chemical weapons materials for export and destruction overseas for the first time in more than two weeks; delay revives concerns about the country's readiness and ability to meet newly extended deadlines for completing the task.
lead_paragraph: The delay raised questions about whether Syria can meet an extended deadline of April 27 to export its chemical weapons arsenal for destruction.

headline.main: Syria Ships Out More Chemicals After a 2-Week Lapse
headline.print_headline: Syria Ships Out More Chemicals After a 2-Week Lapse
